desc: The Programming Club is one of the student academic clubs at RMIT, entirely student managed and university-funded. At The Programming Club, we taught students new and different topics with extracurricular events.

The Information Technology Services hackathon was a 27hr event featuring games, catering and mentoring. As a hackathon it was a lot more laid back as it was intended as a gateway for first and second-year students.

desc: The BiG Day In is a technology conference aimed towards secondary school students to give them an idea of what the technology sector looks like as a career as well as the breadth of opportunities in it.
